# API & Data Fetching Rules

## API Client
- Use Axios instance from `@shared/api/api.ts`
- Never create new Axios instances, always use the shared one
- Configure interceptors in the shared API instance
- Handle errors consistently across the app

## Services
- Create service classes/functions in `entities/*/services/` or `entities/*/api/`
- Services should contain API call logic only
- One service per entity
- Export services from entity `index.ts`

## React Query
- Use React Query (`@tanstack/react-query`) for all client-side data fetching
- Create custom hooks in `entities/*/hooks/` directory
- Use `useQuery` for GET requests
- Use `useMutation` for POST, PUT, DELETE requests
- Always provide query keys following the pattern: `['entity', 'action', ...params]`
- Use `queryClient.invalidateQueries` after mutations

## Data Validation
- Always validate API responses with Zod schemas
- Use `z.infer<typeof schema>` to infer TypeScript types from schemas
- Validate data in React Query hooks using `schema.parse()` or `schema.safeParse()`
- Handle validation errors gracefully

## Error Handling
- Use React Query's built-in error handling
- Provide user-friendly error messages
- Handle network errors, validation errors, and API errors separately
- Use `isAbortErr` utility to check for abort errors

## Request/Response Types
- Define request types in `types/requests/` directory
- Define response types in `types/responses/` directory
- Use Zod schemas to validate both requests and responses
- Export types from entity `index.ts`

## API Patterns
- Use consistent naming: `getEntity`, `createEntity`, `updateEntity`, `deleteEntity`
- Use RESTful conventions for endpoints
- Handle pagination, filtering, and sorting consistently
- Use proper HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)

## Caching
- Configure appropriate cache times for queries
- Use `staleTime` and `cacheTime` appropriately
- Invalidate queries after mutations
- Use optimistic updates when appropriate
